    <string name="privacy_header">Privacy Policy</string>
    <string name="privacy_content">
        StuShare is committed to protecting your privacy.\n\n
        1. INFORMATION COLLECTION\n
        We collect the following information to provide services:\n
        - Personal Information: Name, Email, Profile Picture (when you log in).\n
        - Usage Data: Download history, saved document list.\n\n
        2. PURPOSE OF USE\n
        - Account management and user authentication.\n
        - Improving experience and suggesting relevant documents.\n
        - Sending notifications about important updates.\n\n
        3. DATA SECURITY\n
        All your data is encrypted and stored securely on servers. We apply advanced technical measures to prevent unauthorized access.\n\n
        4. INFORMATION SHARING\n
        We commit NOT to sell, trade, or share your personal information with third parties, unless required by law enforcement.\n\n
        5. YOUR RIGHTS\n
        You have the right to access, correct, or request deletion of your personal data at any time through the Settings section in the application.
    </string>

    <string name="terms_header">Terms of Use</string>
    <string name="terms_content">
        Welcome to StuShare - The Learning Document Sharing Community.\n\n
        1. ACCEPTANCE OF TERMS\n
        By downloading, installing, and using StuShare, you agree to comply with these Terms of Use. If you do not agree, please do not use the application.\n\n
        2. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS\n
        Any document you upload to StuShare must be owned by you or you must have the legal right to share it. You are fully responsible for the copyright of the documents you upload.\n\n
        3. CODE OF CONDUCT\n
        - Do not post content that violates laws, is obscene, incites violence, or insults others.\n
        - No spam or unauthorized advertising.\n
        - Respect the community and other members.\n\n
        4. DISCLAIMER\n
        StuShare is an intermediary sharing platform. We are not responsible for the accuracy or reliability of documents uploaded by users.\n\n
        5. VIOLATION HANDLING\n
        We reserve the right to remove any content that violates terms and lock user accounts without prior notice.
    </string>

